    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-06T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-06T17:00:00-05:00" n="500"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d500">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.CC/10–644: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-06T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 6, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2375. Please deliver immediately the following personal message from the
                    Secretary to Mr. Molotov:</p>
                <p>“As you know from my message of October 2<note n="83" xml:id="d500fn83">See
                        telegram 2340, <ref target="#pg_863">p. 863</ref>.</note> all arrangements
                    have been completed for the publication on October 9 of the joint communiqué and
                    the text of the proposals for an international organization. We feel that any
                    delay in the publication would only result in misunderstanding and speculation,
                    and I therefore urge that, if you have not been able to agree with the British
                    Government on a satisfactory wording for the last paragraph of the communiqué,
                    you consent to the publication of the communiqué omitting the last paragraph
                    entirely in order that we may publish the text and documents on October 9 as
                    agreed. I am sending a similar message to Mr. Eden.”<note n="84"
                        xml:id="d500fn84">Telegram 8181, October 6, 9 p.m., not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
